Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)  climbed to
the highest level in almost two months as Calcalist reported
Vector Capital Corp., a San Francisco-based venture capital
firm, is in talks to buy the computer-service provider for $300
million.  The shares advanced 1.9 percent to 23.22 shekels, the
highest since Feb. 10, at the 4:30 p.m. close in  Tel Aviv .  Calls made to Ness headquarters werenâ€™t answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
